TITLE: Handling YouTube TV OAuth2 Authentication Events in YouTube.js
DESCRIPTION: Code demonstrating how to handle authentication events in the YouTube.js library when using YouTube TV OAuth2. It shows event listeners for pending authentication, successful authentication, and credential updates, followed by the sign-in method call.
SOURCE: https://github.com/luanrt/youtube.js/blob/main/examples/auth/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Fired when waiting for the user to authorize the sign in attempt.
yt.session.on('auth-pending', (data) => {
  // data.verification_url contains the authorization URL.
  // data.user_code contains the code to enter on the website.
});

// Fired when authentication is successful.
yt.session.on('auth', ({ credentials }) => {
  // Do something with the credentials, eg; save them in a database.
  console.log('Sign in successful');
});

// Fired when the access token expires.
yt.session.on('update-credentials', ({ credentials }) => { /** do something with the updated credentials. */ });

await yt.session.signIn(/* credentials */);
```

