TITLE: Defining Channel Class for YouTube Kids API in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This code defines a Channel class that extends the Feed class, specifically for handling YouTube Kids channel data. It includes a constructor, properties for header and contents, and methods for checking continuations and retrieving additional data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/luanrt/youtube.js/blob/main/docs/api/namespaces/YTKids/classes/Channel.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
class Channel extends Feed<IBrowseResponse> {
  header?: C4TabbedHeader;
  contents?: ItemSectionContinuation | ItemSection;

  constructor(actions: Actions, data: ApiResponse | IBrowseResponse, already_parsed = false) {
    super(actions, data, already_parsed);
  }

  async getContinuation(): Promise<Channel> {
    const response = await this.actions.execute(
      this.page.continuation_contents?.continuation_endpoint_type === 'CONTINUATION_TYPE_BROWSE'
        ? 'BrowseEndpoint'
        : 'channelTab',
      this.page.continuation_contents?.continuation
    );

    return new Channel(this.actions, response, false);
  }

  get has_continuation(): boolean {
    return this.page.continuation_contents?.continuation !== undefined;
  }
}
```

