TITLE: Type Introspection and Safe Casting Methods in YTNode Base Class (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet outlines inherited utility methods used by SectionList and other YTNode-derived classes for runtime type checking, casting, and key assertion. Methods such as as(), is(), hasKey(), and key() allow developers to safely transform or verify nodes against specific constructor types, check for property existence, and retrieve optional properties with proper type safety. These generic, TypeScript-centric utilities enable flexible and type-safe manipulation of complex parser node trees typical of the YouTube.js project. Dependencies include definitions for YTNode, YTNodeConstructor, and the Maybe wrapper for optional values.
SOURCE: https://github.com/luanrt/youtube.js/blob/main/docs/api/namespaces/YTNodes/classes/SectionList.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
/**
 * Cast to one of the given types. Throws if node is not of the given type(s).
 */
as<T extends YTNode, K extends YTNodeConstructor<T>[]>(...types: K): InstanceType<K[number]>;

/**
 * Check if the node is of the given type.
 */
is<T extends YTNode, K extends YTNodeConstructor<T>[]>(...types: K): this is InstanceType<K[number]>;

/**
 * Check for a key without asserting the type.
 */
hasKey<T extends string, R = any>(key: T): this is SectionList & { [k in string]: R };

/**
 * Assert that the node has the given key and return it, wrapped in a Maybe.
 */
key<T extends string, R = any>(key: T): Maybe;
```

