TITLE: Extending YTNode with SearchHeader Definition - TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Defines the SearchHeader class that models a YouTube search result header by extending the generic YTNode parser node. The class constructor takes a RawNode from API response data and exposes properties chip_bar and search_filter_button, which represent UI elements if available. This class relies on other parsed node types like ChipCloud and Button, expects integration in the YouTube.js parsing hierarchy, and provides static typing and runtime type-safe methods from YTNode, including property access and type casting. Inputs are API response objects; outputs are structured parser nodes usable in further processing or UI rendering.
SOURCE: https://github.com/luanrt/youtube.js/blob/main/docs/api/namespaces/YTNodes/classes/SearchHeader.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
// src/parser/classes/SearchHeader.ts
import YTNode from '../../Helpers/classes/YTNode';
import ChipCloud from './ChipCloud';
import Button from './Button';
import type { RawNode } from '../../APIResponseTypes/type-aliases/RawNode';

class SearchHeader extends YTNode {
  static type = 'SearchHeader';

  chip_bar: ChipCloud | null;
  search_filter_button: Button | null;

  constructor(data: RawNode) {
    super();
    // Parse chip_bar and search_filter_button from raw data
    this.chip_bar = data.chipBar ? new ChipCloud(data.chipBar) : null;
    this.search_filter_button = data.searchFilterButton ? new Button(data.searchFilterButton) : null;
  }
}

export default SearchHeader;

```

