TITLE: Utility Methods for Type and Key Handling on YTNode - YouTube.js (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript snippet focuses on utility methods provided either by the YTNode superclass or inherited in SearchSuggestionsSection: as<T, K>(), hasKey<T, R>(), is<T, K>(), and key<T, R>(). These method signatures enable safe casting, type checking, and property access for nodes derived from complex YouTube API responses. Required dependencies include YTNodeConstructor, Maybe, and strong typing via generics. All methods accept node type constructors and/or keys as parametersinputs are typically node classes and property strings; outputs provide type assertions or retrieved values, sometimes wrapped in Maybe. Limitations include requiring the correct type relationships at compile time, and they may throw if the type or key is incorrect.
SOURCE: https://github.com/luanrt/youtube.js/blob/main/docs/api/namespaces/YTNodes/classes/SearchSuggestionsSection.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
/**
 * Cast to one of the given types.
 * Throws if the node is not of the given type.
 */
as<T extends YTNode, K extends YTNodeConstructor<T>[]>(...types: K): InstanceType<K[number]>;

/**
 * Check for a key without asserting the type.
 */
hasKey<T extends string, R = any>(key: T): this is this & { [k in string]: R };

/**
 * Check if the node is of the given type.
 */
is<T extends YTNode, K extends YTNodeConstructor<T>[]>(...types: K): this is InstanceType<K[number]>;

/**
 * Assert that the node has the given key and return it.
 * Throws if the node does not have the key.
 */
key<T extends string, R = any>(key: T): Maybe;

```

